description:
What can we learn about soul winning from stories of King Solomon and Solomon's temple in 1 Kings 9 and 10? What can the Queen of Sheba teach us about going from knowing to belief? Why is sharing the truth not enough to convert people? 

The headlines in the news tell us that turmoil and natural disasters are escalating. These are signs fulfilling prophecy, showing that we are living in the gathering time just prior to Christ’s return. We are to bring the Gospel to the world. Have we done our duty?

In “Rise and Shine” Walter Veith presents a typological study of 1 Kings 9 and 10, the stories of God’s appearance to Solomon after he’d built the temple, and of the Queen of Sheba’s visit. Discover the powerful messages God has for us in these familiar stories of King Solomon.
